{"bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":1,"note":"to create pod\nkubectl run <name of pod> --image=<name of the image which kube will create the pod and its container from inside the pod>\n\nto describe pod\nkubectl describe pod <name of pod>\n\nto enter the node(server) of minikube\nminikube ssh or ssh docker@<minikube i.p>\n\nto get minikube i.p\nminikube i.p\n\nto list pods\n\nkubectl get pods\n\nkubectl get pods -o wide (to get full details of pods)\n\nto delete a pod\n\nkubectl delete pod <name of pod>\n\nto creat a deployment using yaml\nk apply -f <name of the yaml file> nb: -f stands for “file”\n\nto list deployments\nk get deploy\n\nto list services\nk get services\n\nto open connection to the deployment\/pod (TO CONNECT FROM AN EXTERNAL SOURCE)\nminikube service <service name>\n\nto delete deploment and service\n\nk delete -f <deployment file name > -f <service file name>\n\n\n\n\n\nto creat a service using yaml\nk apply -f <name of the yaml file> nb: -f stands for “file”\n\nside note****\n\nto build an image intended for your dockerhub, always use your dockerhub “username\/<name of image>”\n\nto push the imahe to your dockerhub repo, use “docker login” and the “docker push <dockerusername\/image name>\n"}